01:08:55.029 --> 01:08:59.029
he credits receiving it to Jehovah,

01:08:59.029 --> 01:09:03.029
and not as a personal achievement.

01:09:03.029 --> 01:09:09.029
So to conclude this portion of our talk about avoiding these peace disturbance,

01:09:09.029 --> 01:09:14.029
we say, may we all strive to be genuine peacemakers,

01:09:14.029 --> 01:09:18.029
analyzing ourselves, praying for Jehovah's spirit,

01:09:18.029 --> 01:09:21.029
to help us to avoid any tendency,

01:09:21.029 --> 01:09:27.029
to be jealous, to envy, or to be contentious with our brothers.

01:09:27.029 --> 01:09:31.029
But now, let's talk about some things we can do personally,

01:09:31.029 --> 01:09:34.029
to promote peace and joy.

01:09:34.029 --> 01:09:37.029
In fact, let's talk quickly about six things we can do.

01:09:38.029 --> 01:09:43.029
Number one, cultivate humility and modesty.

01:09:43.029 --> 01:09:47.029
Humility means to consider others superior to ourselves.

01:09:47.029 --> 01:09:52.029
Modesty means to be aware of our own limitations.

01:09:52.029 --> 01:09:55.029
Now, if we have those two closely related qualities,

01:09:55.029 --> 01:10:00.029
we'll be able to apply Romans chapter 12, verse 3,

01:10:00.029 --> 01:10:05.029
which says we should not think more of ourselves than it is necessary to think,

01:10:05.029 --> 01:10:09.029
but to think so as to have a sound mind.

01:10:09.029 --> 01:10:13.029
And here's the second thing we can do to promote joy and peace.

01:10:13.029 --> 01:10:20.029
Appreciate and value the good qualities and talents of others.

01:10:20.029 --> 01:10:24.029
Focus on their good points, not their flaws.

01:10:24.029 --> 01:10:27.029
And how thankful we can be that Jehovah does that with us.

01:10:27.029 --> 01:10:30.029
Otherwise, we'd be doomed, wouldn't we?

01:10:30.029 --> 01:10:33.029
But maybe you heard the illustration of a brother,

01:10:33.029 --> 01:10:38.029
holding up a white piece of paper with a red spot in the middle

01:10:38.029 --> 01:10:42.029
and asking an audience what they see.

01:10:42.029 --> 01:10:45.029
Well, most say they see a red spot.

01:10:45.029 --> 01:10:51.029
But then he points out that actually 99% of what they're looking at is white paper.

01:10:51.029 --> 01:10:54.029
But we tend to notice the spot.

01:10:54.029 --> 01:10:57.029
Well, if we're not careful, that's what we can do with our brothers.

01:10:57.029 --> 01:10:59.029
No set flaw, rather than all the good qualities.

01:11:00.029 --> 01:11:07.029
But may all of us cultivate the Jehovah-like quality of noticing,

01:11:07.029 --> 01:11:14.029
appreciating and valuing the good qualities of our brothers.

01:11:14.029 --> 01:11:16.029
Now here's the third thing we can do.

01:11:16.029 --> 01:11:21.029
Never presume that fellow Christians are trying to outdo us.

01:11:21.029 --> 01:11:24.029
Verse Corinthians 137 says,

01:11:25.029 --> 01:11:28.029
So we believe, we hope,

01:11:28.029 --> 01:11:33.029
that our brothers are doing what they're doing out of a good motive

01:11:33.029 --> 01:11:36.029
to please Jehovah, not to outdo us.

01:11:36.029 --> 01:11:40.029
And we remember Jehovah's appointed only one judge, Jesus.

01:11:40.029 --> 01:11:47.029
We are no judge, we have no right to negatively judge our brothers' motives.

01:11:47.029 --> 01:11:50.029
Now here's the fourth thing we can do.

01:11:51.029 --> 01:11:57.029
Strive to always rejoice over our brothers' privileges and successes.

01:11:57.029 --> 01:11:59.029
Romans 12, 15.

01:11:59.029 --> 01:12:02.029
Rejoice with those who rejoice.

01:12:02.029 --> 01:12:04.029
Weep with those who weep.

01:12:04.029 --> 01:12:06.029
Now which is easier?

01:12:06.029 --> 01:12:12.029
