Two sentences from this 12th verse here,

01:55:36.189 --> 01:55:38.189
Romans 12, 12,

01:55:38.189 --> 01:55:41.189
and take this to heart.

01:55:41.189 --> 01:55:44.189
Rejoice in the hope,

01:55:44.189 --> 01:55:48.189
endure under tribulation.

01:55:48.189 --> 01:55:51.189
So while waiting for the fulfillment

01:55:51.189 --> 01:55:53.189
of all of Jehovah's promises,

01:55:53.189 --> 01:55:55.189
and the things that we have to deal with,

01:55:55.189 --> 01:55:57.189
remember how Jesus dealt with it,

01:55:57.189 --> 01:56:00.189
just cling to Jehovah,

01:56:00.189 --> 01:56:03.189
have that close relationship with him,

01:56:03.189 --> 01:56:08.189
and you will experience the greatest joy.

01:56:08.189 --> 01:56:11.819
Thank you, Brother Morris,

01:56:11.819 --> 01:56:13.819
for explaining why we find joy

01:56:13.819 --> 01:56:16.819
in walking closely with our Heavenly Father

01:56:16.819 --> 01:56:19.819
as Jesus did.

01:56:19.819 --> 01:56:20.819
We have seen today that our joy

01:56:20.819 --> 01:56:23.819
does not depend on external circumstances.

01:56:23.819 --> 01:56:26.819
Rather, it is a God-given quality,

01:56:26.819 --> 01:56:28.819
and Jehovah has indeed given us

01:56:28.819 --> 01:56:31.819
